# Accessibility Compliance Linter

Ensures all components meet WCAG 2.1 AA standards and provide inclusive user experiences.
Flags accessibility violations and enforces best practices.

## FORBIDDEN PATTERNS:
- ❌ Missing alt text for images and icons
- ❌ Missing ARIA labels for interactive elements
- ❌ Poor color contrast ratios (<4.5:1 for normal text)
- ❌ Missing keyboard navigation support
- ❌ Components that don't respect reduced motion
- ❌ Missing focus indicators
- ❌ Non-semantic HTML structure

## ALLOWED PATTERNS:
- ✅ Proper ARIA labels and descriptions
- ✅ Keyboard navigation support
- ✅ High contrast color schemes
- ✅ Semantic HTML elements
- ✅ Screen reader friendly content
- ✅ Respect for user preferences
- ✅ Clear focus indicators

## EXAMPLES:

### ❌ BAD - Missing accessibility
```tsx
const ToggleButton = () => {
  return (
    <div onClick={toggle}>
      <div className="toggle-slider" />
    </div>
  );
};
```

### ✅ GOOD - Accessible component
```tsx
const ToggleButton = ({ label, checked, onChange }) => {
  return (
    <button
      onClick={onChange}
      aria-label={label}
      aria-pressed={checked}
      className="toggle-button"
      role="switch"
    >
      <span className="sr-only">{label}</span>
      <div className="toggle-slider" />
    </button>
  );
};
```

## ACCESSIBILITY REQUIREMENTS:
- WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
- Keyboard navigation support
- Screen reader compatibility
- High contrast mode support
- Reduced motion respect
- Focus management

## USAGE:
- Runs on all component files
- Integrates with accessibility testing tools
- Provides inline suggestions for improvements